  "prompt": "What are some things new employees should know going into their first day at H&E Equipment Services?",
  "response": "Here are some helpful tips for new employees starting at H&E Equipment Services:\n\n1. Dress Code\n- Likely business casual or work appropriate attire\n- May require safety gear depending on specific role\n- Check employee handbook for specific guidelines\n\n2. First Day Preparation\n- Bring necessary identification documents\n- Have copies of employment paperwork\n- Bring notepad and pen for orientation\n- Be prepared to fill out additional paperwork\n\n3. Workplace Culture\n- Professional but collaborative environment\n- Equipment services industry requires attention to detail\n- Safety is likely a key priority\n- Team-oriented workplace\n\n4. Potential Initial Tasks\n- HR orientation\n- Safety training\n- Company policy review\n- Meeting team members\n- Initial job training\n\n5. Professional Expectations\n- Be punctual\n- Ask questions when unclear\n- Show willingness to learn\n- Demonstrate reliability\n- Follow safety protocols\n\nThese suggestions are general and based on typical onboarding practices. For specific details, it's best to consult H&E Equipment Services' HR department or your direct supervisor.",
